name: Preterm

purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of  values contains a physical exam finding that represents the number of births of a newborn greater than 24 weeks and less than 37 weeks of completed gestation.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify number of births of a newborn greater than 24 weeks and less than 37 weeks of completed gestation.  Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the "Assessment" category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Include SNOMED CT codes that identify number of births of a newborn greater than 24 weeks and less than 37 weeks of completed gestation.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet the inclusion criteria.)
